  "prompt": "Does cctv works during power cut?",
  "response": "Typically, standard CCTV systems rely on power from the electrical grid to operate. Therefore, during a power cut, these systems would stop working unless they have a backup power source. However, there are several ways to ensure that CCTV systems continue to function during a power outage:\n\n1. **Uninterruptible Power Supply (UPS)**: A UPS can provide temporary power to the CCTV system during a power cut. Depending on the capacity of the UPS, it can keep the cameras running for a short duration to ensure continuous monitoring until power is restored.\n\n2. **Battery Backup**: Some advanced CCTV systems come with built-in battery backups. These batteries automatically take over when the main power supply is interrupted, allowing the cameras to continue capturing footage.\n\n3. **Solar Power**: Solar-powered CCTV systems can operate independently of the grid. These systems use solar panels to generate electricity, which can be stored in batteries for use during periods when there is no sunlight or during power cuts.\n\n4. **Generator**: A generator can be used to provide power to a CCTV system during extended power outages. While this solution might be more costly and require maintenance, it ensures that the surveillance system remains operational.\n\nTo ensure your CCTV system is resilient during a power cut, you may consider incorporating one or more of these backup solutions.",
